                <!-- /.card-header -->
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p><b>Course Description:</b> This course covers the concepts of digital logic and switching networks. The course includes the fundamental concepts of boolean algebra and its application for circuit analysis, multilevel gates networks, flip-lops, counters logic devices and synchronous and asynchronous sequential logic and digital integrated circuits.</p><p><br></p><p><b>Course Objectives:</b> The main objective of this course is to introduce the basic tools for the design of digital circuits and introducing methods and procedures suitable for a variety of digital design applications.</p><div><br></div>
                </div>
